          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "**Context:** Discovered while shipping `pd-ocr-trainer-spa` M11 (HF publish path). Spec 09 §5 of pd-ocr-trainer-spa references `pd_book_tools.licenses.SPDX_VALID_IDS` for validating user-supplied license identifiers before publishing datasets/models to the Hugging Face Hub. That constant does not exist, so trainer-spa currently bundles its own hand-rolled SPDX subset in `domain/publish.py` as a stopgap.\n\n**Problem:** Each downstream tool hand-rolling its own license subset will drift — one accepts `Apache-2.0`, another typos it, and nothing catches the mismatch. pd-book-tools is the universal upstream every `pd-*` repo already imports, so it's the cheapest single source of truth.\n\n**Proposed scope (minimal — match what trainer-spa needs today):**\n- New module `pd_book_tools/licenses.py` exposing:\n  - `SPDX_VALID_IDS: frozenset[str]` — the set of valid SPDX license identifiers\n  - a validation helper, e.g. `is_valid_spdx_id(value: str) -> bool`\n- **Data-driven, not hand-maintained.** Vendor the authoritative SPDX license list (JSON) or wrap the `spdx-license-list` / `license-expression` package — do not curate the list by hand.\n- Keep the API **license-domain-generic** (no HF-specific naming) — future consumers below are not HF-related.\n\n**Future consumers (do not build integration now — just don't design HF-specifically):**\n- `pd-ocr-synth` — font licenses in recipes (`OFL-1.1`, etc.) and generated-dataset output license\n- `pd-ocr-training` — `ExportManager` dataset/model-card metadata\n- `pd-prep-for-pgdp` — public-domain rights on PGDP submission packages (`CC0-1.0` / public-domain markers)\n\n**Follow-up after this lands:** `pd-ocr-trainer-spa` drops its local SPDX subset in `domain/publish.py` and imports `SPDX_VALID_IDS` instead.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-22T12:02:15Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Shipped on branch `feat/spdx-license-allowlist` (commit 46be7aa).\n\nNew module `pd_book_tools/licenses.py` exposes:\n- `SPDX_VALID_IDS: frozenset[str]` — 518 valid SPDX licenseId strings\n- `is_valid_spdx_id(value: str) -> bool` — exact, case-sensitive; returns False (no raise) on non-str input\n\nData-driven via vendored `pd_book_tools/data/spdx_licenses.json` (SPDX license-list-data schema), loaded with `importlib.resources`. Chose vendoring over wrapping a pip package so pd-book-tools stays self-contained — a runtime dependency here would land in every consumer's install closure. API is license-domain-generic (no HF-specific naming). Verified the JSON ships in the built wheel.\n\nFollow-up (separate, downstream): pd-ocr-trainer-spa can now drop its hand-rolled SPDX subset in `domain/publish.py` and import `SPDX_VALID_IDS`.",
                "createdAt": "2026-05-22T12:02:14Z",
                "id": "IC_kwDOONYVBs8AAAABDVJYpg",
